- Points: (63.87,16.63), (66.66,42.93), (38.28,45.94), (35.49,19.64) - then path returns to start
- This has 4 distinct vertices = Trapezoid (K)

**CRITICAL - Counterintuitive Pattern from Training Data**: When you encounter a path with multiple M commands, you MUST count every distinct coordinate point that appears in the path, regardless of whether it appears after an M or L command. The M commands indicate pen lifts but do not reduce the vertex count.

