- The second M command goes to (7.85,57.83) which was already visited by the previous L command - this is the SAME point
- Unique coordinates: (72.96,32.63), (7.85,57.83), (39.84,72.32), (52.68,87.15), (58.40,70.53), (81.67,51.69) = 6 unique points
- The path closes back to start (72.96,32.63)
- Answer: 6 vertices = Hexagon (C)

