2. If no arcs, count the TOTAL number of "L" commands in the entire path (across ALL segments, including those after additional "M" commands)
3. Check if the last coordinates match or are close to the first coordinates after the first "M" command (indicating a closed shape)
4. If closed, the total number of "L" commands equals the number of sides
5. Match the number of sides to the polygon name in the options
6. Output ONLY the corresponding letter

