**Task Context:**
You will be analyzing SVG path elements to determine what geometric shape they draw. The text will contain an SVG path with coordinates and will ask what shape is drawn, followed by multiple choice options.

**SVG Path Analysis Guide:**
- SVG paths use commands like "M" (move to) and "L" (line to) followed by coordinate pairs (x,y)
- To count vertices: identify each unique coordinate pair in the path
- The path typically closes when it returns to or near the starting point
- Count ONLY the distinct coordinate points that form the shape's vertices
- If a coordinate appears multiple times (like the starting/ending point), count it only once

**Examples of vertex counting:**
- "M 82.59,29.92 L 82.20,49.38 M 82.20,49.38 L 65.38,41.46 L 64.44,22.89 L 82.59,29.92" has 4 distinct points: (82.59,29.92), (82.20,49.38), (65.38,41.46), (64.44,22.89) → 4-sided shape (quadrilateral/kite)
- "M 26.00,23.00 L 19.00,16.00 L 40.00,74.00 L 83.00,64.00 L 91.00,38.00 L 34.00,12.00 L 26.00,23.00" has 6 distinct points → hexagon
- "M 83.09,23.07 L 79.47,12.76 L 59.24,20.73 L 46.65,15.67 L 62.63,29.74 L 83.09,23.07" has 5 distinct points → pentagon

**Shape to Category Mapping:**
- Triangle (3 vertices) → J
- Quadrilateral/Kite (4 vertices) → D
- Pentagon (5 vertices) → G
- Hexagon (6 vertices) → C
- Heptagon (7 vertices) → B
- Octagon (8 vertices) → F
- Circle → varies by options
- Sector → I
- Line → E
- Rectangle → depends on options (likely K or other)

