**Critical Distinction for Rectangles vs Trapezoids:**
- For a 4-vertex shape to be a rectangle (H), it must have BOTH pairs of opposite sides parallel AND equal in length
- If only one pair of opposite sides is parallel, or if parallel sides have different lengths, it is a trapezoid (K)
